{META_DATA}: KING KONG
{META_DATA}: Written by
{META_DATA}: Fran Walsh, Philippa Boyens and Peter Jackson
{META_DATA}: Based on a Story by
{META_DATA}: Merian C. Cooper and Edgar Wallace
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. CENTRAL PARK - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: A scrawny MONKEY scratches.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLES ON: Defeated, listless ANIMALS, in the bleak environs of a dilapidated ZOO.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WIDER: It is CENTRAL PARK ZOO in depression era NEW YORK.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The PARK itself is like a GARBAGE DUMP, dotted with squalid SHANTY TOWNS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Against these BLEAK IMAGES, the SOUND of a BRIGHT, BRASSY SONG fades up: Al Jolson, singing "I'm Sitting on Top of the World".
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The sky line of MANHATTAN rises in the background, a grim steaming jungle on this cold FALL day.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: I
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. NY STREETS - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LONG continues over:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IMAGES: The CROWDED STREETS of NEW YORK ... beneath the bustle is a sense of despair.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LONG SOUP LINES snake along the STREETS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The HUNGRY search through RUBBISH BINS for FOOD.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SKYSCRAPERS rise steadily upwards as more people are evicted from their homes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HOMELESS sleep amid steaming VENTS and GARBAGE STREWN GUTTERS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Intercut:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. VAUDEVILLE THEATRE - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SONG continues over:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: I
{DIALOGUE}: SANNY, an old-time VAUDEVILLIAN, hurriedly fixes a large DROOPY MOUSTACHE on to a YOUNG WOMAN'S TOP LIP ... this is ANN DARROW.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IMAGES: Weird and wonderful snatches of VAUDEVILLE ACTS follow ... singers, jugglers, boxing ladies.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: E
{DIALOGUE}: Intercut with:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. NY STREETS - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The COLOR and MUSIC contrast with the SOUP LINES and SLUMPED SHOULDERS of the REAL WORLD.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. VAUDEVILLE THEATRE - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: ANN on STAGE ... dressed as an ELEGANT GENT, she launches into `I'm Just Wild About Harry' with HARRY, a larger- than-life PERFORMER dressed in a FRILLY DRESS, BRASSY RED WIG and FALSIES.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 2.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MANNY's CHARACTER joins in ... SNEEZING LOUDLY and causing ANN to take a SUDDEN PRAT FALL.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: nd so the ROUTINE BUILDS ... ANN and HARRY singing and dancing ... MANNY SNEEZING ... ANN falling.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The AUDIENCE look on with bored expressions on their faces.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: All except ONE MAN at the BACK, who is LAUGHING HYSTERICALLY.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: ANN throwing everything into her ACT ... SWEAT rolls down her face ... she tries not to get distracted by the LAUGHING, WHEEZING MAN.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WIDER: A SMATTERING of APPLAUSE from the TINY AUDIENCE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 40 PEOPLE in a THEATRE designed for 500.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Crash cut:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. DRESSING ROOM - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: MANNY in the NOISY, CROWDED DRESSING ROOM, which is full of VAUDEVILLE PERFORMERS in various stages of undress.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MANNY fires off a loud comical SNEEZE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks around at the others.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ANNY
{DIALOGUE}: That's a funny one!
{DIALOGUE}: Isn't that funnier?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HARRY
{DIALOGUE}: It's hysterical, Manny.
{DIALOGUE}: As long as we're laughing we won't be crying over the box office.
{DIALOGUE}: Talk about depressing.
