{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. VENTURE/NY DOCKS - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: JACK emerges from the labyrinthine SHIP INTERIOR and rushes to the RAIL of the SHIP ... he freezes in HORROR!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Oh Christ!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: The SHIP is PULLING AWAY from the DOCK ... 6 feet ... 7 feet ... JACK contemplates JUMPING for a MOMENT:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK (cont'd)
{DIALOGUE}: Goddammit!
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. NY DOCKS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: POLICE CARS race along the docks towards the VENTURE, SIRENS wailing.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. VENTURE DECK - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: JACK SLUMPS on the DECK in DESPAIR.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He's missed his chance to get off the ship.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 26.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: DENHAM steps up behind JACK, just as a POLICE CAR, followed by ZELMAN and the INVESTORS, pull up on the DOCKS in the DISTANCE.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DENHAM
{DIALOGUE}: I keep telling you, Jack, there's no money in theatre.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. NY DOCKS - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The INVESTORS leap out of the car.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SLEAZY INVESTOR
{DIALOGUE}: No, no, no!
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. VENTURE DECK - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The VENTURE steams past the LIGHTS of MANHATTAN.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DENHAM
{DIALOGUE}: You're much better off sticking with film.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: I don't do it for the money, Carl.
{DIALOGUE}: I happen to love the theatre.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DENHAM
{DIALOGUE}: o, you don't.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: JACK looks at him exasperated as DENHAM casually taps his PIPE on the RAIL of the BOAT.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DENHAM (cont'd)
{DIALOGUE}: If you really loved it, you would have jumped.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. NY DOCKS - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WIDE ON: ZELMAN throws his hat to the ground in anger as THE VENTURE pulls away from the docks.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. NEW YORK HARBOUR - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WIDE ON: The VENTURE steams away from the DOCKS, passing under the MANHATTAN BRIDGE.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. ANN'S CABIN - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: ANN tests her mattress with her hands.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANN straightens & turns, perching on the edge of the BUNK.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 27.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PRESTON
{META_DATA}: (apologetic)
{DIALOGUE}: I hope you find it to your liking... it's quite comfortable.
{DIALOGUE}: Your towels and linens are underneath the bed.
{DIALOGUE}: That is the wash basin.
{DIALOGUE}: I know, that's not a pleasant smell - is it?
{DIALOGUE}: I'm sure it'll disperse in a day or two.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: RESTON dances over to the WARDROBE.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PRESTON (cont'd)
{DIALOGUE}: The closet ... your costumes - I hope you'll find everything is in order.
{DIALOGUE}: If there is anything that you need, please do not hesitate to ask...fresh water, perhaps?
{DIALOGUE}: I can bring it to you personally.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: PRESTON is interrupted by a knock on the CABIN DOOR...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: The DOOR opens and DENHAM enters.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He thrusts a bottle of JOHNNY WALKER SCOTCH into ANN'S HANDS ...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DENHAM
{DIALOGUE}: Knock knock!
{DIALOGUE}: We can't have our leading lady deprived of the necessities of life.
{DIALOGUE}: to PRESTON) Do me a favour - run a bottle down to Jack.
{DIALOGUE}: It'll fend off his migraine.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PRESTON
{DIALOGUE}: They're still trying to find a place for him to sleep.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DENHAM
{META_DATA}: (to PRESTON)
{DIALOGUE}: You told him my typewriter is available for hire?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RESTON
{DIALOGUE}: Yes - he didn't take it well.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: PRESTON departs down the corridor.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ANN
{META_DATA}: (confused)
{DIALOGUE}: Mr. Driscoll ...?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: DENHAM turns and looks at ANN.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ANN (cont'd)
{DIALOGUE}: He's on board?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DENHAM
{DIALOGUE}: Jack has his heart set on coming.
{DIALOGUE}: Call me a softie - I couldn't say no.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 28.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. SHIPS HOLD - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: CHOY is showing JACK to his sleeping QUARTERS, carrying BLANKETS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: JACK stares in DISBELIEF at the DINGY HOLD strewn with STRAW BALES and EMPTY ANIMAL CAGES.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He reacts to the SMELL.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHOY
{DIALOGUE}: This room very comfortable, plenty dim light ... fresh straw.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: What'd you keep down here?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHOY
{DIALOGUE}: Lion, tiger, hippo - you name it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jack What, do you sell them to Zoos?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHOY
{DIALOGUE}: Zoos ... circus ...
{META_DATA}: (lowers voice)
{DIALOGUE}: Skipper get big money for rare animal.
{META_DATA}: (alarmed)
{DIALOGUE}: Careful!
{DIALOGUE}: Camel have bad accident on floor.
{DIALOGUE}: Stain unremovable ...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: JACK looks down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He's standing in a dark, viscous PUDDLE OF GUNGE.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHOY (cont'd)
{META_DATA}: (lowers voice)
{DIALOGUE}: Skipper catch any animal you want.
{DIALOGUE}: He do you real good price on rhite wino.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: E ENGLEHORN
{META_DATA}: (sternly)
{DIALOGUE}: Choy!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: CHOY clams up as ENGLEHORN strolls into the hold.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ENGLEHORN (cont'd)
{DIALOGUE}: My apologies for not being able to offer you a cabin.
{DIALOGUE}: Have you found an enclosure to your taste?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{META_DATA}: (dryly)
{DIALOGUE}: Spoilt for choice.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ENGLEHORN surveys a COUPLE OF LARGE CAGES.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ENGLEHORN
{DIALOGUE}: What are you, Mr. Driscoll, a lion or a chimpanzee?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: JACK opens a CAGE large enough to sleep in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 29.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Maybe, I'll take this one.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He steps back with SURPRISE as a WOODEN CRATE TOPPLES, spilling out a LARGE MEDICAL BOTTLE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CHOY looks up in SHOCK as the BOTTLE ROLLS towards ENGLEHORN who coolly TRAPS it with his FOOT.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: E ENGLEHORN
{DIALOGUE}: I told you to lock it up.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHOY
{META_DATA}: (scared)
{DIALOGUE}: Sorry, Skipper!
{DIALOGUE}: Lumpy said -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ENGLEHORN
{META_DATA}: (interrupts)
{DIALOGUE}: Lumpy doesn't give the orders.
{DIALOGUE}: What are you trying to do?
{DIALOGUE}: Put the whole ship to sleep?
{DIALOGUE}: Get them out of here!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ENGLEHORN hands the BOTTLE to a nervous CHOY.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: JACK stares at the CRATES stacked in the CAGE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: Piles of BOTTLES, all marked "Chloroform".
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. VENTURE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WIDE ON: The VENTURE ploughs through a HEAVY SWELL.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BRUCE'S CABIN - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: NGLE ON: BRUCE pins movie posters from some of his previous films on his cabin wall ... He steps back, admiring them.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. SHIPS HOLD - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: JACK, sitting in the hold, TAPPING on an OLD TYPEWRITER propped up on BOXES.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is clearly very QUEASY, as he tries to stay focussed on the TYPEWRITER KEYS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He sees JIMMY carrying a TRAY come into view, he COUGHS and CLAMS UP.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JIMMY
{DIALOGUE}: Compliments of the chef -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: JIMMY unloading the BOWLS of GREY looking STEW from the TRAY.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LOSE ON: JIMMY puts the BOWL next to JACK ... who takes one look at it, and SQUEEZES his eyes closed.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: Oh Christ - oh God!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JIMMY
{DIALOGUE}: Lambs brains in walnut sauce.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 30.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The CAGES and ROPES SWAY with each roll of the WAVES ... JIMMY walks away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: JACK looking very nauseated ...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HAYES (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: Jimmy!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: JIMMY spins round, a guilty look on his face.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HAYES (cont'd)
{DIALOGUE}: You run those ropes up on deck like I told you?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JIMMY
{DIALOGUE}: Doing it now, Mr. Hayes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: JIMMY tries to slip past, but HAYES grabs his WRIST.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HAYES
{DIALOGUE}: How about you return Mr. Driscoll's pen first?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: An expensive FOUNTAIN PEN drops from JIMMY'S HAND and clatters to the floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: QUICK as an eel, JIMMY scampers AWAY.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HAYES shakes his head, and picks up the PEN ... hands it back.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HAYES (cont'd)
{DIALOGUE}: He doesn't mean any harm.
{DIALOGUE}: I'll keep him out of Jyour way.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ACK
{DIALOGUE}: No, it's okay.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HAYES
{DIALOGUE}: It's just he likes it down here, it's where I found him ... four years ago ... stowed away in one of them cages.
{DIALOGUE}: His arm was broken in two places, he was wilder than half the animals in here.
{DIALOGUE}: Still won't tell me where he came from - all I know, it wasn't any place good.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. VENTURE DECK - DAY
