{CHARACTER_NAME}: DENHAM
{DIALOGUE}: All right everyone, from the top.
{DIALOGUE}: And ... action!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: BRUCE saunters up to ANN, who is leaning on the rail, staring out to sea, in full hair and make-up.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ANN
{DIALOGUE}: I think this is awfully exciting!
{DIALOGUE}: I've never been on a ship before.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUCE
{DIALOGUE}: I've never been on one with a woman before.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ANN
{DIALOGUE}: I guess you don't think much of women on ships, do you?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUCE
{DIALOGUE}: No, they're a nuisance.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: DENHAM looking intently at JIMMY and HAYES who are further down the DECK ... talking quietly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 37.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: HAYES shoots DENHAM an ALARMED LOOK.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ANN (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: Well, I'll try not to be.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUCE (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: Just being around is trouble.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ANN (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: Well!
{DIALOGUE}: Is that a nice thing to say!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUCE (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: It's a dangerous thing, having girls on ships.
{DIALOGUE}: They're messy and they're unreliable!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DENHAM
{META_DATA}: (distracted)
{DIALOGUE}: Cut!
{DIALOGUE}: Great!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: NGLE ON: DENHAM'S gaze returns to JIMMY and HAYES who are huddled in a group with three more SAILORS ... word is travelling fast.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DENHAM (cont'd)
{DIALOGUE}: Bruce, wonderful performance.
{DIALOGUE}: You can relax for ten minutes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: BRUCE looking pretty pleased with himself.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DENHAM (cont'd)
{DIALOGUE}: That was very natural... I felt moved.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: JACK looks on in disbelief.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: B
{DIALOGUE}: ANGLE ON: BRUCE walking past JACK ...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RUCE
{DIALOGUE}: hat do you think, Driscoll?
{DIALOGUE}: The dialogue's got some flow now - huh?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: It was pure effluence.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUCE
{DIALOGUE}: beefed up the banter ...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Try to resist that impulse.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUCE
{DIALOGUE}: It's just a little humor, Bud - what are you, a Bolshevik or something?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: JACK watches as BRUCE saunters off ... he turns back to DENHAM.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Actors.
{DIALOGUE}: They travel the world but all they ever see is a mirror!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 38.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: JACK looks up to see ANN looking dismayed, a MIRROR COMPACT, in her hand ...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She quickly snaps the COMPACT shut and turns away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON: JACK - taken aback.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. SHIP'S CORRIDOR - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANN is making her way to the BATHROOM.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She looks up as JACK rounds a corner coming the other way.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They walk toward each other.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SUDDENLY the ship sways, JACK is thrown forward, but ANN manages to hold her BALANCE.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Good legs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANN looks at him SHARPLY.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK (cont'd)
{DIALOGUE}: Sea legs - I meant - you know ... sea legs.
{DIALOGUE}: Not that you don't have good legs, I was just ...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: JACK trails off as ANN edges past him, averting her eyes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK (cont'd)
{DIALOGUE}: ... making conversation.
{DIALOGUE}: Jesus!
{META_DATA}: (calling)
{DIALOGUE}: Miss Darrow!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANN stops and turns ...
