{CHARACTER_NAME}: LUMPY
{DIALOGUE}: I would say they was full of it, Mr. Hayes.
{DIALOGUE}: We turned south-west last night.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LOSE ON: DENHAM looks up sharply ... HAYES is standing over him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DENHAM
{DIALOGUE}: Gentlemen please, we're not looking for trouble -
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON: JIMMY enters the MESS from behind him...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JIMMY
{DIALOGUE}: No.
{DIALOGUE}: You're looking for something else ...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: PRESTON glances warily at DENHAM.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: DENHAM takes in the situation and decides to front up.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DENHAM
{META_DATA}: (quietly)
{DIALOGUE}: Yes ....
{DIALOGUE}: we are.
{DIALOGUE}: We're gonna find Skull Island!
{DIALOGUE}: We're gonna find it, film it and show it to the world.
{DIALOGUE}: For twenty five cents you get to see the last blank space on the map!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LUMPY
{DIALOGUE}: I wouldn't be so sure of that.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PRESTON
{DIALOGUE}: What do you mean?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LUMPY
{DIALOGUE}: Seven years ago, me and Mr Hayes - we were working our passage on a Norwegian barque.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HAYES
{DIALOGUE}: We picked up a castaway - found him in the water - he'd been drifting for days.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LUMPY
{DIALOGUE}: His ship had run aground on an island, way West of Sumatra.
{DIALOGUE}: An island hidden in fog.
{DIALOGUE}: He spoke of a huge wall, built so long ago - no one knew who had made it ... A wall a hundred foot high ... as strong today as it was, ages ago.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PRESTON
{DIALOGUE}: Why did they build the wall?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SILENCE ...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 42.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LUMPY
