{CHARACTER_NAME}: C
{DIALOGUE}: LOSE ON: KONG stares at the small figure in his hand who is waiting for DEATH to come.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In this moment an UNFAMILIAR feeling wells inside him ... a half formed emotion he hasn't experienced much in his long life: he feels a connection to this tiny creature.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The SPARK of RAGE goes out in KONG'S EYES ...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: KONG stares at ANN as a confusion of feelings wash over him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ONG pulls back from ANN ... overcome by sudden UNCERTAINTY.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He knows only that she has somehow disarmed him ... and this has in turn, DIMINISHED his power.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: KONG starts to BACK AWAY from ANN - slowly at first, until DOUBT and FEAR compel him to move faster.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Suddenly he turns away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANN watches as KONG lopes off.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He pulls himself up and over a RUINED WALL and DISAPPEARS from SIGHT.
